msgid "<1.so>Carry my thoughts...<2.pa>to him..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: sound
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: choice
msgctxt "talk01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm? <2.pa>Do you have a wish for the water\n"
"fairy too?\n"
"\n"
"Oh... I suppose not. <3.pa>If you did,\n"
"you'd have a letter to send.\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>But wait, does that mean you're...<5.pa>\n"
"a servant of the water fairy?!<6.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
msgctxt "talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>OH, WOW! If that's the case, I have an\n"
"important request for you!\n"
"\n"
"Once I release it, I'd like you to follow\n"
"my <2.se_co>love letter <3.re_co>and get to know whoever\n"
"picks it up.\n"
"<4.so>Once you do that, please report back to\n"
"me so I can find out what kind of person\n"
"he is..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: single_choice
#. 6: sound
#. 7: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I know, I know. You're probably thinking,\n"
"\"Why not just go yourself, lazy girl?!\"<2.pa>\n"
"I'm right, aren't I?\n"
"The thing is, I promised my mother\n"
"I wouldn't venture out too far.\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>So I'm begging you. Please...<4.pa> Find the\n"
"person who picks up this letter. OK?<5.si_ch>\n"
"\n"
"<6.so>Tee hee!<7.pa> Thank you!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Excellent! OK, I'm going to throw the\n"
"letter in now!<2.pa> Are you ready?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh. Sure, I can wait...<2.pa>\n"
"But please make it quick!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid ""
"<1.so>These letter containers <2.se_co>break easily<3.re_co>,<4.pa>\n"
"so please be careful."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk07"
msgid "<1.so>Oh, you..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That can't possibly be so...<2.pa> Please don't\n"
"make fun of me just because I'm a\n"
"cute girl."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid "<1.so>If you're a traveler, that's lucky for me!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: raw
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid "<1.so>Hm? What is it?<2.ra>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk100"
msgid "<1.so>Good morning."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk101"
msgid "<1.so>Hello."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk102"
msgid "<1.so>Good evening."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk103"
msgid "<1.so>Hey!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: choice
msgctxt "talk104"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Sorry for the random question,<2.pa> but have\n"
"you ever been to <3.se_co>Zora's Domain<4.re_co>?<5.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk105"
msgid "<1.so>I see... <2.pa>Is it far from here?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: pause (longer)
#. 5: sound
#. 6: sound
#. 7: pause (short)
#. 8: set_colour (red)
#. 9: reset_colour
#. 10: set_colour (blue)
#. 11: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk106"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I see...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Oh! <3.pa>Sorry.<4.pa> I forgot to introduce myself.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>I am Sasan, the traveling merchant.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<6.so>I was on my way to Zora's Domain...<7.pa>\n"
"but a <8.se_co>love letter <9.re_co>in this inlet caught\n"
"my eye.\n"
"The writer seems to be a lovely Zora\n"
"named Finley.\n"
"\n"
"I've been corresponding with her by\n"
"giving my replies to travelers heading\n"
"to <10.se_co>Zora's Domain<11.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk107"
msgid ""
"<1.so>A mysterious letter from a Zora woman...<2.pa>\n"
"Intriguing, is it not?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk108"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Unfortunately, I can't tell you what she\n"
"wrote. <2.pa>A gentleman would never read\n"
"a lady's letter to a stranger.\n"
"<3.so>But I CAN assure you that she writes in\n"
"the sweetest, most refined way ever.<4.pa>\n"
"She must be a very elegant young lady.\n"
"Actually, as a Zora, she's probably a lot\n"
"older than me.<5.pa> That doesn't bother me\n"
"one bit, but...<6.pa>I hope she feels the same."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk109"
msgid "<1.so>I see... <2.pa>Very well then."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Right...<2.pa> As I was saying:<3.pa> please follow\n"
"that letter. And don't let it break!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk111"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So then... <2.pa>Next it's her turn to write,<3.pa>\n"
"so I'll just wait here awhile."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: single_choice
msgctxt "talk113"
msgid "<1.so>So...<2.pa>you were following this letter?<3.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: sound
#. 7: pause (short)
#. 8: choice
msgctxt "talk114"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm, so she asked you to come down\n"
"here and see what kind of person I am.<2.pa>\n"
"Is that it?\n"
"<3.so>Well, earlier I lied when I wrote to her\n"
"that I was a buff traveler. <4.pa>She said she\n"
"wanted to meet me, but...\n"
"Even though I'm dying to meet her,<5.pa>\n"
"I can't do it.\n"
"\n"
"<6.so>I've really blown it.<7.pa> If I had known this\n"
"would happen—that I'd fall for her—\n"
"I never would've lied...<8.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk115"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Love reigns supreme... <2.pa>Hmm. I suppose\n"
"it does.<3.pa> Ya know, hearing that does make\n"
"me feel a little better."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk116"
msgid ""
"<1.so>This could work...<2.pa> I guess I just have to\n"
"start pumping up my muscles now..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: sound
#. 5: sound
#. 6: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk119"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>Ahhh!!<3.te_si>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>I worked really hard on that letter...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>But it's OK...<6.pa> It's not like you did it\n"
"on purpose or anything.\n"
"\n"
"I bet I could be even more eloquent than\n"
"that anyway, so I'll just start over and\n"
"write a new letter... "
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: pause (longer)
#. 7: sound
#. 8: pause (short)
#. 9: sound
#. 10: sound
#. 11: sound
#. 12: sound
#. 13: pause (short)
#. 14: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>For Zora girls, there's a superstition that\n"
"if you send a <2.se_co>love letter<3.re_co> from the\n"
"<4.se_co>Bank of Wishes<5.re_co> and get a response...\n"
"You'll have good fortune for life!<6.pa>\n"
"Who doesn't want that?!\n"
"\n"
"<7.so>And after many attempts...<8.pa>\n"
"I finally got a response!\n"
"\n"
"<9.so>Of course, I'm no chump and certainly\n"
"no fool. I wasn't hatched yesterday!\n"
"\n"
"I need to know what kind of person my\n"
"mystery man is. That's why I desperately\n"
"want to meet him.\n"
"<10.so>Thing is, my mom told me not to venture\n"
"too far, and I agree going on my own is\n"
"a dumb idea. I'm not sure what to do.\n"
"<11.so>Hmmm... He described himself as,\n"
"\"a buff and super gorgeous traveler.\"\n"
"Gosh, I hope THAT'S the truth.\n"
"<12.so>And with that delicate penmanship,<13.pa>\n"
"I suspect he's quite refined.<14.pa>\n"
"Regal, even!\n"
"If he's a Hylian, I do hope he's OK with\n"
"being with a Zora who's considerably\n"
"older than him. Wiser too, no doubt.\n"
"Hey, love requires an open mind,\n"
"wouldn't you say?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: text_size
#. 3: text_size
#. 4: pause (longer)
#. 5: sound
#. 6: sound
#. 7: pause (short)
#. 8: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk121"
msgid ""
"<1.so><2.te_si>AHHH!!<3.te_si>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"I worked SO hard on that letter! <4.pa>And now\n"
"I have to write ANOTHER one?\n"
"\n"
"<5.so>*sigh* Oh, well. \n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<6.so>After all, they say the more you have\n"
"to struggle for love, the sweeter it is.<7.pa>\n"
"Hee hee, yeah... <8.pa>That must be true."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: raw
#. 5: set_colour (blue)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: pause (long)
#. 8: sound
#. 9: pause (longer)
#. 10: set_colour (blue)
#. 11: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk122"
msgid ""
"<1.so>OK! <2.pa>It's time for me to take a chance\n"
"and try to meet her...\n"
"\n"
"Oh, that reminds me...<3.pa> I wonder if the\n"
"torrential rain has stopped.<4.ra>She's waiting in <5.se_co>Zora's "
"Domain<6.re_co>.<7.pa>\n"
"That's what her letter says, anyway.\n"
"\n"
"<8.so>So I'll achieve two goals at the same\n"
"time and train up my muscles on\n"
"the way there! I'll get super beefy!\n"
"Yeah, that's the ticket! I'll run all the way\n"
"to the domain!<9.pa> Catch ya later!\n"
"\n"
"We'll meet again at <10.se_co>Zora's Domain<11.re_co>—\n"
"I'm sure of it!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk123"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh!<2.pa> It's you!\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Hey, Sasan!<3.pa> This is the guy who made\n"
"sure my letter reached you safely!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: sound
#. 7: pause (short)
#. 8: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk124"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh! <2.pa>It's you!<3.pa> As you can see, I somehow\n"
"made it to <4.se_co>Zora's Domain<5.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"<6.so>Thanks to you, I managed to work up the\n"
"courage<7.pa> to finally meet Finley.<8.pa> At least,\n"
"that's how I see it."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk125"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Thank you so much for introducing me\n"
"to my soul mate!\n"
"\n"
"Sasan and I discussed it, and we decided\n"
"we just HAD to thank you the next time\n"
"we saw you.\n"
"So here... This is from both of us.\n"
"Thank you for everything!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk126"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Sasan! <2.pa>Be sure to swim and climb and lift\n"
"and stuff. A LOT. <3.pa>That will help you build\n"
"up those muscles you promised me!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk127"
msgid ""
"<1.so>As you wish...<2.pa>my darling...<3.pa>\n"
"I'll try my best..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm Finley.<2.pa> I came from <3.se_co>Zora's Domain<4.re_co>.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"My mother and father are so busy,\n"
"we rarely spend time together anymore.<5.pa>\n"
"I spend most days in solitude."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk14"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You lost sight of my <2.se_co>love letter<3.re_co>,\n"
"didn't you?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I understand.<2.pa> These containers break\n"
"really easily, so please be careful."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: raw
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid "<1.so>Do you have any other questions?<2.ra>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Luckily, I thought something like that\n"
"might happen, so I made an extra."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "talk22"
msgid "<1.so>Oh, really?!<2.pa> How lucky!"
msgstr ""

